{
  "If f(x) = x^2 - 6x + 11, what x-value gives the minimum?": "",
  "-3": "",
  "6": "",
  "11": "",
  "3": "",
  "For f(x) = x^2 - 6x + 11, the vertex is at x = -b/(2a) = 6/2 = 3. Since a > 0 the parabola opens upward, so x = 3 gives the minimum.": "",
  "What is the maximum value of f(x) = -2x^2 + 8x + 1?": "",
  "9": "",
  "4": "",
  "8": "",
  "1": "",
  "Vertex at x = -8/(2(-2)) = 2. f(2) = -2(4) + 8(2) + 1 = -8 + 16 + 1 = 9. Since a < 0, the parabola opens downward and 9 is the maximum.": "",
  "To find the critical points of a function, you set which expression equal to zero?": "",
  "The original function f(x)": "",
  "The second derivative f''(x)": "",
  "The derivative f'(x)": "",
  "The integral of f(x)": "",
  "Critical points occur where f'(x) = 0 or f'(x) is undefined. Setting the first derivative equal to zero locates candidates for local maxima and minima.": "",
  "Two positive numbers have a sum of 20. What values maximize their product?": "",
  "8 and 12": "",
  "1 and 19": "",
  "10 and 10": "",
  "5 and 15": "",
  "Let the numbers be x and 20 - x. Product P = x(20 - x) = 20x - x^2. Maximum at x = 10, giving P = 100. Equal numbers maximize the product for a fixed sum.": "",
  "If the derivative changes from positive to negative at x = c, then f(c) is a:": "",
  "Local minimum": "",
  "Inflection point": "",
  "Local maximum": "",
  "Saddle point": "",
  "When f'(x) changes from positive to negative at x = c, the function goes from increasing to decreasing. By the First Derivative Test, f(c) is a local maximum.": "",
  "What is the minimum value of f(x) = x^2 + 4x + 7?": "",
  "-2": "",
  "7": "",
  "Vertex at x = -4/2 = -2. f(-2) = 4 - 8 + 7 = 3. Since a = 1 > 0, the parabola opens upward and the minimum value is 3.": "",
  "If f'(x) = 3x^2 - 12, what are the critical points?": "",
  "x = 2 and x = -2": "",
  "x = 0 only": "",
  "x = 4 and x = -4": "",
  "x = 6 and x = -6": "",
  "Set f'(x) = 0: 3x^2 - 12 = 0, so x^2 = 4, giving x = 2 and x = -2.": "",
  "A rectangle has a perimeter of 40 cm. What dimensions maximize its area?": "",
  "18 cm by 2 cm": "",
  "10 cm by 10 cm": "",
  "12 cm by 8 cm": "",
  "15 cm by 5 cm": "",
  "With perimeter 2l + 2w = 40, so l + w = 20. Area A = l(20 - l) is maximized when l = 10, giving a 10 by 10 square with area 100 cm^2.": "",
  "If f''(c) > 0 at a critical point x = c, the function has a:": "",
  "Vertical asymptote": "",
  "Point of inflection": "",
  "By the Second Derivative Test, if f'(c) = 0 and f''(c) > 0, the function is concave up at x = c, so f(c) is a local minimum.": "",
  "What is the maximum product of two numbers whose sum is 30?": "",
  "200": "",
  "210": "",
  "225": "",
  "250": "",
  "P = x(30 - x) = 30x - x^2. Maximum at x = 15, so P = 15 * 15 = 225.": "",
  "What is a 'critical point' of a function?": "",
