  "A point where the function equals zero": "",
  "A point where the second derivative equals zero": "",
  "A point where the function is discontinuous": "",
  "A critical point is a value in the domain of f where f'(x) = 0 or f'(x) does not exist. These are the candidates for local extrema.": "",
  "What does the term 'optimization' mean in mathematics?": "",
  "Graphing a function on a coordinate plane": "",
  "Simplifying a complex expression": "",
  "Finding the domain of a function": "",
  "Finding the maximum or minimum value of a function subject to constraints": "",
  "Optimization is the process of finding the best (maximum or minimum) value of a function, often subject to given constraints or conditions.": "",
  "What does the 'First Derivative Test' determine?": "",
  "Whether a function is continuous": "",
  "The concavity of a function": "",
  "Whether a critical point is a local max, local min, or neither": "",
  "The exact value of a limit": "",
  "The First Derivative Test examines the sign change of f'(x) around a critical point to classify it as a local maximum, local minimum, or neither.": "",
  "What is a 'constraint' in an optimization problem?": "",
  "The function to be maximized or minimized": "",
  "The graph of the function": "",
  "The derivative of the objective function": "",
  "A condition or restriction that limits the possible solutions": "",
  "A constraint is a condition (such as a fixed perimeter, budget, or material amount) that restricts which values the variables can take in an optimization problem.": "",
